name: Team Tile
description:
This is a multi-tiled acrylic painting done by Muffin Man, Mori, & Jobz. It's simple, clean, & a combination of all 3 artist's throw-ups on one canvas. It originally was a skateboard design but then later was recreated on canvas.
Size: 15x20

name: Forever On Point
description:
Muffin Man believes in this city you must be "forever on point". This phrase means to be aware of the dangers & risks that come with this lifestyle. Graffiti may result in arrest, conviction, & even time in prison. Late nights put you in risks of the dangers of the street. You must always have an eye open & be aware of your surroundings. You never know who is watching. Who will try to hurt you. Everything from law enforcement, thugs, business owners, & canary pedestrians can result in immediate restraint. So be on point!
Size: 7x5
FYI: This is the very first illustration of Muffin's pencil character & is a 100% original peice.

name: I Bake NY
description:
This acrylic canvas speaks for itself. Muffin Man has put this mark all throughout NYC. The muffin. Or the cupcake. OR is it a muffin with frosting? Whatever it is, Muffin Man sure muffs NY.
Size: 19x15

name: Desert Dessert + Lil' Miss Muffin
description:
These are Muffin Man's first animations of female characters.

"Desert Dessert": This acrylic canvas serves as symbolism of graffiti as crime. The more art you create the more you are just feeding this monster that will constantly need to be fed. You always have to keep relevance & creation in effect. The monster symbolizes the City of New York. The cactuses symbolize the hardness of the law, & if you cut through it you will be able to quench your thirst. The desert symbolises the wide range of canvas you have to use in this city. Other depiction's as the "Chanel" print read "CG" on the bandana which stands for CowGirl & Cupcake Girl. IT has an urban western feel.
Size: 5x4 (Isle Included!)

"Lil' Miss Muffin": This is an illustration of Muffin's love for femininity. The outfit depicted as follows: a queen crown, a cherry pattern bandana, drippy frosting & sprinkle crop top, & a cupcake wax paper bottom high-rise skirt. The paper bags are puppets which are symbolizing the characterization & taunting of the law.
Size: 7x5 (Isle Included!)

FYI: These canvases are $50 each

name: Japan Relief
description:
Graffiti Artists Muffin Man, Seso, & Peek collaborated on an acrylic painting after the Tsunami hit Japan in March 2011. This is a historical & original piece depicting an incorporation of both Pok√©mon Jigglypuff & Pikachu, Lettering, Tags, & The Japan flag in the background. It was hung at the 3rd Eye Solation Gallery in Brooklyn, NY during a Japan Relief show.

Size: 15x20
